        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "This document presents a reproducible analysis workflow for examining population records by **Thana**, **City Corporation classification**, and **Age Group**. The experiment focuses on cleaning location labels, separating records into areas inside and outside the City Corporation, summarizing population counts, and calculating percentage distributions.\n",
        "\n",
        "The analysis uses a cleaned Excel dataset loaded from an environment variable. The workflow is designed to support transparent reporting, verification, and future replication without hard-coding the input file path.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "The main objectives of this experiment are to:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Load the cleaned dataset from a configured environment path.\n",
        "- Remove records from Thanas that are outside the intended analysis scope.\n",
        "- Standardize inconsistent or alternative Thana names through mapping.\n",
        "- Classify Thanas into City Corporation and non-City Corporation groups.\n",
        "- Create an age-based grouping using a threshold of 30 years.\n",
        "- Produce total population counts and Thana-wise summaries.\n",
        "- Calculate percentage distributions for City Corporation, outside City Corporation, and overall dataset shares.\n",
        "- Run a verification check to confirm whether all records are accounted for in the final grouping.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Data Loading and Preparation"
      ],
      "id": "a159bdc0"
    },
